1
00:00:06,465 --> 00:00:08,008
It's fine.

2
00:00:09,426 --> 00:00:11,428
Everything's fine.

3
00:00:11,512 --> 00:00:13,805
Nothing's wrong. It's all fine.

4
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:16,308
Excuse me, what day is it?

5
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:19,811
-Saturday.
-Saturday. Good.

6
00:00:19,895 --> 00:00:21,563
Good. I like Saturdays.

7
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:25,317
-So I just met Rose Tyler?
-Yeah.

8
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,611
But she's locked away
in a parallel world.

9
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:30,989
Exactly. If she can cross from her
parallel world to your parallel world

10
00:00:31,073 --> 00:00:33,575
then that means the walls of
the universe are breaking down,

11
00:00:33,659 --> 00:00:36,828
which puts everything in danger.
Everything.

12
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,706
But how?

13
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:14,741
Thing is, Doctor,
no matter what's happening,

14
00:01:14,825 --> 00:01:17,369
and I'm sure it's bad, I get that.

15
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:22,541
But Rose is coming back.

16
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:25,085
Isn't that good?

17
00:01:26,587 --> 00:01:27,671
Yeah.

18
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,798
(EXPLOSION)

19
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:34,511
-What the hell was that?
-Don't know. It came from outside.

20
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:43,103
But we're in space.

21
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:45,188
How did it happen?

22
00:01:45,272 --> 00:01:47,524
What did you do?

23
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,820
We haven't moved. We're fixed.

24
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:55,699
It can't have. No!

25
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:02,039
Tardis is still in the same place,
but the Earth has gone.

26
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:04,499
The entire planet!

27
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:07,210
It's gone.

28
00:02:12,716 --> 00:02:17,554
MAN: Give me a cigarette. Right now.
Confirm all stations still online.

29
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:20,641
Can anyone hear me?
Have we got contact with UNIT base...

30
00:02:20,724 --> 00:02:24,186
-What was that?
-WOMAN: Emergency systems online.

31
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,937
Was it some sort of earthquake or...

32
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:28,023
WOMAN: Get the system operational...

33
00:02:28,106 --> 00:02:31,693
-Jalandra, are you all right?
-Yeah, I'm okay.

34
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:33,654
Is anyone hurt?

35
00:02:33,737 --> 00:02:35,697
MARTHA: We've lost power.
Someone get the lights back on.

36
00:02:35,781 --> 00:02:38,075
DaCosta, see to it right now.

37
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:40,786
Suzanne, are you okay?

38
00:02:41,745 --> 00:02:45,374
-Martha, look at the sky.
-Why, what is it?

39
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,709
Just look at the sky!

40
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:51,755
Whoa, what happened?

41
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:55,509
Is it the rift? Gwen, Ianto, you okay?

42
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:58,970
No broken bones. Slight loss of dignity.
No change there, then.

43
00:02:59,096 --> 00:03:02,265
The whole of the city must've felt that.
The whole of South Wales.

44
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:04,601
I'm gonna take a look outside.

45
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:13,318
A little bit bigger than South Wales.

46
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:19,282
Luke, are you all right?

47
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:25,080
It felt like some sort of
cross-dimensional spatial transference.

48
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:28,875
But it's night. It wasn't night.
It was 8:00 in the morning!

49
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:30,627
Mr Smith, I need you!

50
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:36,758
I wish you'd stop giving that fanfare
and just tell me what happened!

51
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:39,803
Sarah Jane, I think
you should look outside.

52
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:43,348
I'll think you'll find
the visual evidence most conclusive.

53
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:48,895
It's gone dark.
It's them aliens, I'll bet my pension.

54
00:03:48,979 --> 00:03:51,481
What do you want this time,
you green swine?

55
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,735
-Dad...
-Look, you get back inside, Sylvia.

56
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:58,905
-They always want the women.
-No, Dad, just look. Oh, my God!

57
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:01,324
Look at the sky!

58
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:05,662
That's impossible.

59
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:07,372
That's just impossible.

60
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:11,251
It can't be.

61
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:31,813
Right, now we're in trouble.

62
00:04:31,897 --> 00:04:33,482
(COCKING GUN)

63
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:36,151
And it's only just beginning.

64
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:44,826
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

65
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:30,372
But if the Earth's been moved,
they've lost the Sun.

66
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:33,708
What about my mum? And Granddad?

67
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:35,335
They're dead!

68
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:37,921
Are they dead?

69
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:42,175
I don't know, Donna. I just don't know.
I'm sorry, I don't know.

70
00:05:42,259 --> 00:05:45,762
That's my family. My whole world.

71
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:48,431
There's no readings. Nothing.

72
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,559
Not a trace.

73
00:05:50,642 --> 00:05:54,187
Not even a whisper.
Oh, that is fearsome technology.

74
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:58,400
-So what do we do?
-We've got to get help.

75
00:05:58,483 --> 00:05:59,901
From where?

76
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,447
Donna, I'm taking you
to the Shadow Proclamation.

77
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,617
Hold tight.

78
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:16,001
The United Nations have issued an edict

79
00:06:16,126 --> 00:06:20,005
asking the citizens of the world
not to panic.

80
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:24,050
So far there has been
no explanation of the 26 planets

81
00:06:24,134 --> 00:06:26,136
which have appeared in the sky.

82
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,638
But it's an empirical fact.

83
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:31,433
The planets didn't come to us,
we came to them.

84
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:33,226
Just look at the stars.

85
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:37,731
We're in a completely different
region of space. We've travelled.

86
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:40,901
Do you know what? I look up and
there's all these moons and things...

87
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:43,778
Have you seen them? Do you see them?

88
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:47,282
What was I drinking last night?
Furniture polish?

89
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,119
Ianto. Time and a place.

90
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:54,080
-Yeah, it's funny, though.
-Gwen, come and see.

91
00:06:54,164 --> 00:06:56,833
Rhys, I have no idea. Just stay indoors.

92
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:59,419
Can you phone my mother? Tell her...

93
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:03,673
Oh, I don't know. Just tell her
to take her pills and go to sleep.

94
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:06,635
I'm gonna come home as soon as I can.

95
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:08,386
I promise.

96
00:07:09,054 --> 00:07:11,556
I love you, you big idiot.

97
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:14,392
JACK: Someone's established
an artificial atmospheric shell,

98
00:07:14,476 --> 00:07:16,186
keeping the air and holding in the heat.

99
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,688
IANTO: Whoever's done this
wants the human race alive.

100
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,690
That's a plus.

101
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:23,693
Twenty-seven planets,
including the Earth.

102
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:27,656
No, but what's that?

103
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:29,741
That's not a planet!

104
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:33,203
MR SMITH: The reading seems to be
artificial in construction.

105
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,790
Some sort of space station,
sitting at the heart of the web.

106
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:39,334
They're fine. Maria and her dad,
they're still in Cornwall.

107
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:42,379
I told them to stay indoors.
Clyde's all right, he's with his mum.

108
00:07:42,504 --> 00:07:46,508
Sarah Jane,
I have detected movement. Observe.

109
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:48,802
Spaceships.

110
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:54,516
Tracking 200 objects.
Earthbound trajectory.

111
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,893
Geneva is calling a Code Red.

112
00:07:57,227 --> 00:07:59,312
Everyone to battle positions.

113
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:02,399
Dr Jones, if you're not too busy...

114
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:05,068
-I'm trying to phone the Doctor, sir.
-And?

115
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:08,613
There's no signal. This number
calls anywhere in the universe.

116
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:12,158
It never breaks down.
They must be blocking it.

117
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:13,785
Whoever they are.

118
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:17,622
We're about to find out.
They're coming into orbit.

119
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:23,586
I'll take you on! Yeah, you, mate!

120
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:27,173
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

121
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:42,814
The end of the world, darling.

122
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:45,108
End of the stinking world.

123
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,527
Have one on me, mate.

124
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:49,112
(GLASS BREAKING)

125
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:50,780
(CAR ALARM BLARING)

126
00:08:59,289 --> 00:09:04,002
Right. You two, you can put
that stuff down or run for your lives.

127
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:07,797
Do you like my gun?

128
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:16,514
We're now getting confirmed reports
of spaceships.

129
00:09:16,598 --> 00:09:19,100
The Pentagon has issued
an emergency report.

130
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,644
Dad, come and see.

131
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:24,606
They're saying spaceships.

132
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,649
-Did you find her?
-No.

133
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:28,651
No, there's no reply.

134
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:31,112
Where are you, Donna?

135
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:33,990
-ANNOUNCER: ...and stay indoors.
-Where are you, sweetheart?

136
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:38,828
3,000 miles and closing.
But who are they?

137
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:41,164
(PHONE RINGING)

138
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:45,585
Martha Jones, voice of a nightingale.
Tell me you put something in my drink.

139
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:48,046
No such luck. Have you heard
from the Doctor?

140
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:50,673
-Not a word. Where are you?
-New York.

141
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:53,426
-Oh. Nice for some.
-I've been promoted.

142
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,595
Medical Director on Project Indigo.

143
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:58,223
Did you get that thing working?

144
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:01,392
Indigo's top secret.
No one's supposed to know about it.

145
00:10:01,476 --> 00:10:03,937
I met a soldier in a bar. Long story.

146
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,647
-When was that?
-Strictly professional.

147
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:09,734
1,500 miles, boys.
And accelerating. They're almost here.

148
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:13,655
I'm receiving a communication
from the Earthbound ships.

149
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:15,865
They have a message for the human race.

150
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,784
Put it through. Let's hear it.

151
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,788
Exterminate! Exterminate!

152
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:24,040
Exterminate!

153
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,126
Exterminate!

154
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,419
Exterminate!

155
00:10:28,503 --> 00:10:30,296
-Exterminate!
-No.

156
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,881
Exterminate!

157
00:10:32,382 --> 00:10:34,050
Exterminate!

158
00:10:34,134 --> 00:10:35,593
-Oh, no.
-Exterminate!

159
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:38,388
What is it? Who are they?
Do you know them, Jack?

160
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:42,433
Exterminate! Exterminate!

161
00:10:43,101 --> 00:10:44,727
Exterminate!

162
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,896
Exterminate!

163
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:49,524
-No.
-Exterminate!

164
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:52,986
-There's nothing I can do.
-Exterminate! Exterminate!

165
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:56,114
-I'm sorry. We're dead.
-Exterminate!

166
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:59,576
-Exterminate!
-Oh, God, you're so young.

167
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:03,079
Exterminate! Exterminate!

168
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:06,916
Exterminate! Exterminate!

169
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,919
-Get out of here! Come on!
-This way. Come on!

170
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:11,880
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

171
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:39,199
Dalek fleet in battle formation.

172
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:42,827
All systems locked and primed.

173
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,914
Crucible at 90% efficiency.

174
00:11:45,997 --> 00:11:48,583
The human harvest will commence.

175
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:52,337
Battle stations!

176
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,881
Geneva declaring ultimate Code Red.

177
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:58,134
Ladies and gentlemen, we are at war.

178
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:20,531
Supreme Dalek on the bridge.

179
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:27,205
SUPREME DALEK:
Soon the crucible will be complete.

180
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:31,584
We have waited long
for this ultimate destiny.

181
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:35,797
Now the Daleks are the masters of Earth.

182
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:40,385
ALL: Daleks are the masters of Earth!

183
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:43,179
Daleks are the masters of Earth!

184
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:51,187
So, go on, then.
What is the Shadow Proclamation anyway?

185
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:55,066
Posh name for police.
Outer-space police. Here we go!

186
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:18,172
Sco bo tro no flo jo ko fo to do.

187
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:21,884
No bo ho sho ko ro to so.

188
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:23,803
Bo-ko-do-zo-go-bo-fo-po-jo.

189
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:29,642
Mo ho.

190
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:32,687
Time Lords are the stuff of legend.

191
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:35,606
Belong in the myths and whispers
of the higher species.

192
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:38,818
You cannot possibly exist.

193
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,863
Yeah. More to the point,
I've got a missing planet.

194
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:44,824
Then you're not as wise
as the stories would say.

195
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,826
The picture is far bigger
than you imagine.

196
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:49,912
The whole universe is
in outrage, Doctor.

197
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:54,250
Twenty-four worlds
have been taken from the sky.

198
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:55,835
How many?

199
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:57,879
Which ones? Show me!

200
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:01,799
Locations range far and wide.

201
00:14:01,883 --> 00:14:04,969
They all disappeared at the exact
same moment, leaving no trace.

202
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:09,057
Callufrax Minor. Jahoo. Shallacatop.
Woman Wept.

203
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:11,851
Clom! Clom's gone! Who'd want Clom?

204
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:14,187
All different sizes.

205
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:17,523
Some populated, some not.
But all unconnected.

206
00:14:17,607 --> 00:14:21,235
-What about Pyrovillia?
-Who is the female?

207
00:14:21,319 --> 00:14:25,615
Donna. I'm a human being.
Maybe not the stuff of legend,

208
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:28,826
but every bit as important
as Time Lords, thank you.

209
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:33,039
Way back, when we were in Pompeii,
Lucius said Pyrovillia had gone missing.

210
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:36,376
Pyrovillia is cold case. Not relevant.

211
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:38,044
How do you mean, cold case?

212
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,588
The planet Pyrovillia
cannot be part of this.

213
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:43,800
-It disappeared over 2,000 years ago.
-Yes, yes, hang on.

214
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,344
But there's
the Adipose Breeding Planet, too.

215
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:50,890
Miss Foster said that was lost.
But that must have been a long time ago.

216
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:53,601
That's it! Donna, brilliant!

217
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:56,896
Planets have been taken
out of time as well as space.

218
00:14:56,979 --> 00:14:58,815
Put this into 3D.

219
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:03,319
Now, if we add Pyrovillia

220
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:07,573
and Adipose III.

221
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:12,578
Something missing.
Where else, where else, where else?

222
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:16,082
Lost, lost, lost, lost.
Oh! The lost moon of Poosh!

223
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:26,467
-What did you do?
-Nothing.

224
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:31,264
The planets rearranged themselves
into the optimum pattern. Ooh.

225
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:33,516
Look at that.

226
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:37,228
Twenty-seven planets in perfect balance.

227
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,855
Come on, that is gorgeous.

228
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:41,858
Oi, don't get all spaceman.
What does it mean?

229
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:45,611
All those worlds fit together
like pieces of an engine.

230
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,030
It's like a powerhouse.

231
00:15:48,573 --> 00:15:51,951
-What for?
-Who could design such a thing?

232
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:55,121
Someone tried to move the Earth
once before.

233
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:57,498
Long time ago.

234
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:01,043
It can't be.

235
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:04,964
DALEK: Maximum extermination!

236
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,720
MAN: The shields are down!
There's too many of them! Abandon ship!

237
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:12,054
The Valiant's down!

238
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:15,224
Air force retreating over North Africa.
Daleks landing in Japan.

239
00:16:15,308 --> 00:16:17,310
GWEN: We've lost contact
with the Prime Minister's plane.

240
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:20,480
-Jack! Manhattan!
-Martha, get out of there.

241
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:22,482
I can't, Jack. I've got a job to do.

242
00:16:22,565 --> 00:16:25,485
They're targeting military bases,
and you're next on the list.

243
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:28,362
Dr Jones, you will come with me.

244
00:16:28,446 --> 00:16:31,616
Project Indigo is being activated.

245
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:33,284
Quick march.

246
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:37,580
But we can't use Project Indigo.

247
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:40,750
It hasn't been tested, sir.
We don't even know if it works.

248
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:45,588
DALEK:
Human forces will be exterminated!

249
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:48,090
Annihilate UNIT!

250
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:57,642
Exterminate!

251
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:07,735
Put it on. Fast as you can!

252
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:13,241
Martha, I'm telling you.
Don't use Project Indigo. It's not safe!

253
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:16,536
You take your orders from UNIT,
Dr Jones, not from Torchwood.

254
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:18,621
-But why me?
-You're our only hope

255
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:23,209
of finding the Doctor.
But failing that, if no help is coming,

256
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:27,463
then with the power invested in me
by the Unified Intelligence Taskforce

257
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:29,924
I authorise you to take this.

258
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,843
The Osterhagen Key.

259
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:35,721
I can't take that, sir.

260
00:17:35,805 --> 00:17:37,682
You know what to do!

261
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:40,309
For the sake of the human race.

262
00:17:41,686 --> 00:17:43,396
(EXPLOSION)

263
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:47,108
DALEK: Dalek Attack Squad Five
reaching north corridor.

264
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,402
-Dr Jones.
-Exterminate! Exterminate!

265
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:51,404
-Good luck.
-Exterminate!

266
00:17:58,953 --> 00:18:00,538
Exterminate!

267
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,832
-Bye, Jack.
-Martha, don't do it!

268
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,336
Don't!

269
00:18:10,548 --> 00:18:12,341
What's Project Indigo?

270
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:14,343
MAN: UNIT base...

271
00:18:14,427 --> 00:18:18,180
Experimental teleport
salvaged from the Sontarans.

272
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:20,933
But they haven't got coordinates
or stabilisation!

273
00:18:21,017 --> 00:18:23,185
So where is she?

274
00:18:23,269 --> 00:18:25,187
Scattered into atoms.

275
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:27,982
Martha's down.

276
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:31,652
Commence the landings.

277
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:34,030
Bring the humans here.

278
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:36,365
Prepare the crucible.

279
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:39,410
VOICE: Supreme Dalek, is there news?

280
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:42,204
SUPREME DALEK:
Earth has been subjugated.

281
00:18:43,039 --> 00:18:46,584
VOICE: I mean, is there news of him?

282
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:50,880
SUPREME DALEK:
Negative. No reports of Time Lord.

283
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:53,883
We are beyond the Doctor's reach.

284
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,551
VOICE: Fascinating.

285
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:59,764
If I had not elevated you
beyond crude emotions,

286
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:03,726
I could almost mistake that tone
for one of victory.

287
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:06,312
Beware your pride.

288
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:09,023
SUPREME DALEK:
The Doctor cannot stop us.

289
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:13,277
VOICE: And yet Dalek Caan is uneasy.

290
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:19,659
SUPREME DALEK:
The abomination is insane!

291
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:25,122
VOICE: Show respect. Without Dalek Caan
none of this would be possible.

292
00:19:25,206 --> 00:19:27,458
And he speaks only the truth.

293
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:30,211
DALEK CAAN: He is coming.

294
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,505
The three-fold man,

295
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:36,258
he dances in the lonely places.

296
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:40,054
Oh, creator of us all

297
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:42,807
the Doctor is coming!

298
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:44,266
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

299
00:19:58,781 --> 00:20:01,951
(HEART BEATING)

300
00:20:10,418 --> 00:20:12,461
You need sustenance.

301
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:14,755
Take the water. It purifies.

302
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:16,799
Thanks.

303
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:19,468
There was something on your back.

304
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:22,471
How did you know that?

305
00:20:22,596 --> 00:20:24,932
You are something new.

306
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:26,642
Not me.

307
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:31,731
I'm just a temp.
Shorthand, filing, 100 words per minute.

308
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:36,485
Fat lot of good that is now.
I'm no use to anyone.

309
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,612
I'm so sorry for your loss.

310
00:20:40,156 --> 00:20:41,365
Yeah.

311
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:45,161
My whole planet's gone.

312
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,872
I mean the loss that is yet to come.

313
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,501
God save you.

314
00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:57,423
Donna, think, Earth. There must
have been some sort of warning.

315
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,759
Was anything happening back in your day,

316
00:20:59,842 --> 00:21:02,803
like electrical storms,
freak weather, patterns in the sky?

317
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:05,014
Well, how should I know?

318
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:08,225
Erm, no. I don't think so. No.

319
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:12,646
-Okay, never mind.
-Although...

320
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:15,816
There were the bees disappearing.

321
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,860
The bees disappearing?

322
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:20,362
The bees disappearing.

323
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:23,073
The bees disappearing!

324
00:21:23,157 --> 00:21:26,410
-How is that significant?
-On Earth, we have these insects.

325
00:21:26,494 --> 00:21:28,287
Some people said it was pollution
or mobile phone signals.

326
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:31,624
-Or they were going back home.
-Back home where?

327
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:33,709
Planet Melissa Majoria.

328
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:37,463
-Are you saying bees are aliens?
-Don't be so daft. Not all of them.

329
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:40,674
But if the migrant bees felt something
coming, some danger, and escaped...

330
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:42,802
-Tandocca!
-The Tandocca Scale.

331
00:21:42,885 --> 00:21:44,553
The Tandocca Scale
is a series of wavelengths

332
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:46,347
used as carrier signals by migrant bees.

333
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,057
Infinitely small.
No wonder we didn't see it.

334
00:21:48,182 --> 00:21:49,767
It's like looking for
a speck of cinnamon in the Sahara.

335
00:21:49,892 --> 00:21:52,394
Look! There it is! The Tandocca trail!

336
00:21:52,478 --> 00:21:54,730
The transmat that moved the planets
was using the same wavelength.

337
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:56,190
We can follow the path!

338
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:58,400
DONNA: And find the Earth!
Well, stop talking and do it!

339
00:21:58,484 --> 00:21:59,777
DOCTOR: I am!

340
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:04,907
We're a bit late.

341
00:22:05,825 --> 00:22:08,327
The signal's scattered but it's a start.

342
00:22:10,955 --> 00:22:13,082
I've got a blip! It's just a blip,
but it's definitely a blip.

343
00:22:13,207 --> 00:22:15,584
Then according to the strictures
of the Shadow Proclamation,

344
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:18,671
I will have to seize your transport
and your technology.

345
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:20,422
Oh, really? What for?

346
00:22:20,548 --> 00:22:22,925
The planets were stolen
with hostile intent.

347
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:24,802
We are declaring war, Doctor.

348
00:22:24,927 --> 00:22:29,098
Right across the universe.
And you will lead us into battle!

349
00:22:29,849 --> 00:22:32,059
Right. Yes.

350
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:35,521
Of course I will.

351
00:22:36,146 --> 00:22:39,817
I'll just go and get you the key.

352
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,992
(WHOOSHING)

353
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:49,910
Doctor, come back!

354
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:54,874
By the holy writ
of the Shadow Proclamation,

355
00:22:54,957 --> 00:22:57,334
I order you to stop!

356
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,920
All humans will leave their homes.

357
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,797
All humans will leave their homes.

358
00:23:01,881 --> 00:23:06,802
The males, the females, the descendents,

359
00:23:06,886 --> 00:23:08,804
you will come with us!

360
00:23:08,888 --> 00:23:11,390
Resistance is useless.

361
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:16,061
-Where are you taking us?
-Daleks do not answer human questions.

362
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:18,063
Stand in line!

363
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:20,107
Dad, please, come home.

364
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:22,568
-They're leaving our street alone.
-I've got a weapon.

365
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:24,987
-It's a paint gun.
-Exactly.

366
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:28,741
Them Dalek things,
they've only got one eye.

367
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:31,327
A good splodge of paint,
they'd be blinded.

368
00:23:31,452 --> 00:23:34,496
We're not going! Do you hear me?

369
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:36,916
Laura, get back inside the house.

370
00:23:36,999 --> 00:23:39,084
Simon, get inside! Go!

371
00:23:42,296 --> 00:23:43,964
Get back in the sky!

372
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:47,301
Get back where you came from
and leave us alone!

373
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:52,014
Dalek attack formation seven.

374
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:58,687
Maximum extermination!

375
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:09,657
-They're monsters.
-Please, Dad, come on.

376
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:16,622
Halt! You will come with me.

377
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:18,248
Will I heck!

378
00:24:22,503 --> 00:24:25,381
My vision is not impaired!

379
00:24:25,506 --> 00:24:27,049
I warned you, Dad.

380
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:31,637
Hostility will not be tolerated!
Exterminate! Exterminate!

381
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,138
Exter...

382
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:44,233
Do you wanna swap?

383
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,318
You're Donna Noble's family, right?

384
00:24:46,402 --> 00:24:48,737
I'm Rose Tyler. And I need you.

385
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:52,992
Yeah, I've tried calling her,
but I can't get through.

386
00:24:53,075 --> 00:24:54,743
But she's still with the Doctor.

387
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:58,163
I know that much.
And the last time she phoned,

388
00:24:58,247 --> 00:25:01,417
it was from a planet called Midnight,
made of diamonds.

389
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:05,379
-What the hell are you two on about?
-Look, she's out there, sweetheart.

390
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:07,256
Your daughter.

391
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:09,842
She's travelling the stars
with that Doctor.

392
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:12,469
-She always has been.
-Don't be ridiculous.

393
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:14,722
Oh, come on, open your eyes.
Look at the sky.

394
00:25:14,805 --> 00:25:19,393
Look at... Look at the Daleks.
You can't start denying things now.

395
00:25:19,476 --> 00:25:21,186
You were my last hope.

396
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:24,773
If we can't find Donna,
we can't find the Doctor.

397
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,820
Where is he?

398
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,701
(THUMPING)

399
00:25:40,456 --> 00:25:43,459
-It's stopped.
-What do you mean?

400
00:25:44,543 --> 00:25:48,047
Is that good or bad? Where are we?

401
00:25:48,130 --> 00:25:49,923
The Medusa Cascade.

402
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:03,020
I came here when I was just a kid,

403
00:26:03,145 --> 00:26:04,980
90 years old.

404
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:09,651
It was the centre of a rift
in time and space.

405
00:26:09,735 --> 00:26:13,614
So, where are the 27 planets?

406
00:26:13,697 --> 00:26:15,783
Nowhere.

407
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,910
The Tandocca trail stops dead.

408
00:26:21,538 --> 00:26:23,499
End of the line.

409
00:26:24,458 --> 00:26:26,251
So what do we do?

410
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:30,005
Doctor, what do we do?

411
00:26:32,216 --> 00:26:34,343
Now, don't do this to me.

412
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:38,680
No, don't.

413
00:26:39,223 --> 00:26:41,183
Don't do this to me.

414
00:26:41,809 --> 00:26:43,769
Not now.

415
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:46,271
Tell me what are we going to do.

416
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:51,401
You never give up.

417
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:54,113
Please!

418
00:27:01,161 --> 00:27:04,456
This is the Commander General
of the United Nations

419
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:06,750
calling the Dalek fleet.

420
00:27:06,834 --> 00:27:10,504
We surrender. Repeat, we surrender.

421
00:27:11,046 --> 00:27:13,340
Planet Earth surrenders.

422
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:15,801
DALEX: ...humans selected for testing

423
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:19,555
will follow Dalek instructions.

424
00:27:19,638 --> 00:27:22,474
The Daleks reign supreme.

425
00:27:22,558 --> 00:27:24,977
All hail the Daleks!

426
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:30,649
You will obey Dalek instructions
without question.

427
00:27:30,732 --> 00:27:33,485
You will obey your Dalek.

428
00:27:33,569 --> 00:27:36,113
(TRANSMISSION SPUTTERING)

429
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:42,703
WOMAN: Can anyone hear me?

430
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:47,249
The Subwave Network is open.
You should be able to hear my voice.

431
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:50,752
Is there anyone there?

432
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:52,588
I know that voice.

433
00:27:53,130 --> 00:27:56,592
-Who's that?
-Some poor soul calling for help.

434
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:59,803
-There's nothing we can do.
-But look at Mr Smith.

435
00:27:59,887 --> 00:28:02,973
MR SMITH: Processing incoming Subwave.

436
00:28:03,056 --> 00:28:05,517
WOMAN: This message is of
the utmost importance.

437
00:28:05,601 --> 00:28:07,561
We haven't much time.

438
00:28:08,604 --> 00:28:10,439
Can anyone hear me?

439
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,901
Someone's trying to get in touch.

440
00:28:14,276 --> 00:28:17,029
The whole world's crying out.
Just leave it.

441
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:19,740
Captain Jack Harkness, shame on you!

442
00:28:20,282 --> 00:28:22,492
Now, stand to attention, sir.

443
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:25,037
What?

444
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:27,080
Who is that?

445
00:28:28,582 --> 00:28:31,376
Harriet Jones, former Prime Minister.

446
00:28:31,627 --> 00:28:33,587
Yeah, I know who you are.

447
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:37,007
Harriet, it's me!
It's me! She can't hear me.

448
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:38,759
Have you got a webcam?

449
00:28:38,884 --> 00:28:41,970
No, she wouldn't let me.
She said they're naughty.

450
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:43,597
I can't speak to her then, can I?

451
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:48,435
Sarah Jane Smith, 13 Bannerman Road,
are you there?

452
00:28:48,518 --> 00:28:50,646
Yeah, yeah, I'm here. That's me!

453
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:52,064
Good!

454
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:54,191
Now, let's see
if we can talk to each other.

455
00:28:58,612 --> 00:29:01,657
The fourth contact seems to be having
some trouble getting through.

456
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:03,659
That's me! Harriet, that's me!

457
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:05,911
I'll just boost the signal.

458
00:29:06,620 --> 00:29:07,913
Hello?

459
00:29:08,664 --> 00:29:10,040
Martha Jones!

460
00:29:10,165 --> 00:29:13,168
-Who's she? I want to get through.
-Martha, where are you?

461
00:29:13,252 --> 00:29:15,587
I guess Project Indigo
was more clever than we thought.

462
00:29:15,671 --> 00:29:18,006
One second I was in Manhattan...

463
00:29:19,049 --> 00:29:22,052
Next second, maybe Indigo
tapped into my mind

464
00:29:22,135 --> 00:29:25,555
'cause I ended up
in the one place I wanted to be.

465
00:29:28,141 --> 00:29:29,476
Mum?

466
00:29:32,688 --> 00:29:34,273
You came home.

467
00:29:34,356 --> 00:29:37,359
At the end of the world,
you came back to me.

468
00:29:38,568 --> 00:29:42,030
But then all of a sudden,
it's like the laptop turned itself on.

469
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:44,533
It did. That was me.

470
00:29:45,701 --> 00:29:49,788
-Harriet Jones, former Prime Minister.
-Yes, I know who you are.

471
00:29:49,871 --> 00:29:53,292
I thought it was about time
we all met given the current crisis.

472
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:56,211
Torchwood, this is Sarah Jane Smith.

473
00:29:56,336 --> 00:29:59,798
I've been following your work.
Nice job with the Slitheen.

474
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:02,551
Yeah, well, I've been staying away
from you lot.

475
00:30:02,634 --> 00:30:04,303
Too many guns.

476
00:30:04,386 --> 00:30:07,889
All the same,
might I say, looking good, ma'am?

477
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,267
Really? Ooh!

478
00:30:10,392 --> 00:30:12,269
Not now, Captain.

479
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:15,981
And Martha Jones,
former companion to the Doctor.

480
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:19,443
-Oi, so was 1!
-But how did you find me??

481
00:30:19,568 --> 00:30:22,904
This, ladies and gentlemen,
this is the Subwave Network.

482
00:30:23,155 --> 00:30:25,699
A sentient piece of software
programmed to seek out

483
00:30:25,782 --> 00:30:29,202
anyone and everyone
who can help to contact the Doctor.

484
00:30:29,286 --> 00:30:31,955
-What if the Daleks can here us?
-No.

485
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:35,584
That's the beauty of the Subwave.
It's undetectable.

486
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:38,837
-And you invented it?
-I developed it.

487
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:41,465
It was created
by the Mr Copper Foundation.

488
00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:44,092
Yeah, but what we need right now
IS a weapon.

489
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:46,470
Martha, back at UNIT,
what did they give you?

490
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:48,638
What was that key thing?

491
00:30:49,222 --> 00:30:50,557
The Osterhagen Key.

492
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,976
That key is not to be used, Dr Jones.

493
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:55,812
Not under any circumstances.

494
00:30:55,937 --> 00:30:57,814
But what is an Osterhagen Key?

495
00:30:57,898 --> 00:31:00,776
Forget about the key!
And that's an order!

496
00:31:00,901 --> 00:31:02,861
HARRIET: All we need is the Doctor.

497
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:05,655
Oh, excuse me, Harriet,
but well, the thing is,

498
00:31:05,781 --> 00:31:08,033
if you're looking for the Doctor,
didn't he depose you?

499
00:31:08,116 --> 00:31:09,326
He did.

500
00:31:09,409 --> 00:31:12,871
And I've wondered about that
for a long time, whether I was wrong.

501
00:31:12,954 --> 00:31:15,082
But I stand by my actions to this day

502
00:31:15,207 --> 00:31:19,544
because I knew... I knew that one day,
the Earth would be in danger.

503
00:31:19,628 --> 00:31:22,422
And the Doctor would fail to appear.

504
00:31:22,547 --> 00:31:25,175
I told him so myself,
and he didn't listen.

505
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,718
But I've been trying to find him.

506
00:31:26,802 --> 00:31:29,304
The Doctor's got my phone on the Tardis,
but I can't get through.

507
00:31:29,388 --> 00:31:31,390
Nor me. And I was here first.

508
00:31:31,473 --> 00:31:34,684
That's why we need the Subwave.
To bring us all together.

509
00:31:35,060 --> 00:31:38,480
Combine forces.
The Doctor's secret army.

510
00:31:39,606 --> 00:31:42,401
Wait a minute.
We boost the signal, that's it.

511
00:31:43,151 --> 00:31:45,737
We transmit that telephone number
through Torchwood itself,

512
00:31:45,821 --> 00:31:48,990
-using all the power of the rift...
-And we've got Mr Smith.

513
00:31:49,116 --> 00:31:51,827
He can link up with
every telephone exchange on the Earth.

514
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:54,746
He can get the whole world to call
the same number all at the same time.

515
00:31:54,830 --> 00:31:57,124
Billions of phones
calling out all at once!

516
00:31:57,207 --> 00:31:59,918
Brilliant! Who's the kid?

517
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:01,795
That's my son.

518
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:03,422
Excuse me, sorry.

519
00:32:03,505 --> 00:32:05,549
Sorry, hello. Ianto Jones.

520
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:08,969
If we start transmitting,
then this Subwave Network

521
00:32:09,052 --> 00:32:12,097
is going to become visible,
I mean, to the Daleks.

522
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:14,349
Yes, and they'll trace it back to me.

523
00:32:14,433 --> 00:32:16,226
But my life doesn't matter.

524
00:32:16,351 --> 00:32:18,353
Not if it saves the Earth.

525
00:32:19,104 --> 00:32:22,065
-Ma'am.
-Thank you, Captain.

526
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:25,277
But there are people out there dying
on the streets.

527
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:28,697
-Marvellous woman. I voted for her.
-You did not!

528
00:32:29,072 --> 00:32:31,825
Now, enough of words, let's begin.

529
00:32:36,246 --> 00:32:38,206
Grid power activated.

530
00:32:38,874 --> 00:32:41,084
All terminals coordinated.

531
00:32:50,010 --> 00:32:53,597
National Grid online,
giving you everything we've got.

532
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,892
-Connecting you to Mr Smith.
-All telephone networks combined.

533
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:01,146
Sending you the number now.

534
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:02,355
(PHONE DIALLING)

535
00:33:02,439 --> 00:33:07,861
Opening Subwave Network to maximum.

536
00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:09,738
Mr Smith?

537
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:12,115
Make that call.

538
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,993
MR SMITH: Galling the Doctor.

539
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:16,411
So am 1.

540
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:21,249
And sending!

541
00:33:43,104 --> 00:33:44,439
(PHONE RINGING)

542
00:33:44,523 --> 00:33:46,441
-Phone!
-Phone!

543
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,569
Martha, is that you?

544
00:33:49,653 --> 00:33:52,531
-It's just a signal.
-Can we follow it?

545
00:33:52,614 --> 00:33:54,324
Just watch me.

546
00:33:55,951 --> 00:34:00,455
Emergency! Unknown network detected!
Subwave frequency!

547
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:05,126
SUPREME DALEK: Find the point of origin.
Find and exterminate!

548
00:34:05,210 --> 00:34:07,963
VOICE: I warned you, Supreme One.

549
00:34:08,088 --> 00:34:11,091
Just as Dalek Caan foretold.

550
00:34:11,216 --> 00:34:14,761
The children of time
are moving against us.

551
00:34:14,844 --> 00:34:18,557
But everything is falling into place.

552
00:34:25,188 --> 00:34:27,148
I think we got a fix!

553
00:34:27,232 --> 00:34:29,317
Mr Smith now at 200%.

554
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:35,657
Come on, Doctor!

555
00:34:46,751 --> 00:34:49,504
(WHISPERING) Find me, Doctor.

556
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:51,423
Find me.

557
00:34:52,382 --> 00:34:54,426
Got it! Locking on.

558
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:03,852
Harriet, a source's locked onto
your location.

559
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:05,478
They found you.

560
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:09,274
I know. I'm using the network
to mask your transmission. Keep going.

561
00:35:09,357 --> 00:35:10,900
Exterminate!

562
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:20,035
DOCTOR: We're travelling through time.

563
00:35:20,994 --> 00:35:24,497
One second in the future.
The phone call's pulling us through.

564
00:35:27,584 --> 00:35:29,294
Captain,

565
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:33,006
I'm transferring the Subwave Network
to Torchwood.

566
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:34,841
You're in charge now.

567
00:35:34,924 --> 00:35:37,260
And tell the Doctor from me,

568
00:35:37,344 --> 00:35:39,554
he chose his companions well.

569
00:35:40,722 --> 00:35:42,140
It's been an honour.

570
00:35:42,223 --> 00:35:43,683
(EXPLOSION)

571
00:35:51,524 --> 00:35:53,902
Harriet Jones, former Prime Minister.

572
00:35:54,027 --> 00:35:57,530
Yes, we know who you are!

573
00:35:58,490 --> 00:36:00,950
Oh, you know nothing of any human.

574
00:36:01,034 --> 00:36:03,370
And that will be your downfall.

575
00:36:04,788 --> 00:36:07,082
Exterminate!

576
00:36:16,966 --> 00:36:20,345
Three, two, one!

577
00:36:20,428 --> 00:36:22,555
(BOTH YELLING)

578
00:36:37,445 --> 00:36:39,489
Twenty-seven planets.

579
00:36:40,448 --> 00:36:42,200
And there's the Earth.

580
00:36:43,076 --> 00:36:45,078
But why couldn't we see them?

581
00:36:45,161 --> 00:36:48,373
The entire Medusa Cascade
has been put a second out of sync

582
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:49,958
with the rest of universe.

583
00:36:50,083 --> 00:36:53,920
Perfect hiding place. Tiny little pocket
of time, but we found them!

584
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:55,547
Ooh, ooh.

585
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,507
Ooh, what's that?

586
00:36:57,632 --> 00:36:59,592
Hold on, hold on.

587
00:36:59,676 --> 00:37:01,636
Some sort of Subwave Network.

588
00:37:04,431 --> 00:37:07,350
Where the hell have you been?
Doctor, it's the Daleks!

589
00:37:07,475 --> 00:37:09,227
Oh, he's a bit nice.
I thought he'd be older.

590
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:10,562
He's not that young.

591
00:37:10,645 --> 00:37:12,897
SARAH JANE: It's the Daleks, they're
taking people to their spaceship...

592
00:37:12,981 --> 00:37:14,941
(ALL TALKING AT ONCE)

593
00:37:15,024 --> 00:37:16,443
...it's not just Dalek Caan!

594
00:37:16,526 --> 00:37:19,237
-That's Donna!
-That's my girl!

595
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,489
Sarah Jane! Who's that boy?

596
00:37:22,031 --> 00:37:23,950
That must be Torchwood.

597
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:27,829
Aren't they brilliant?
Look at you all, you clever people.

598
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:32,417
That's Martha. And who's he?

599
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:35,003
Captain Jack. Don't. Just...

600
00:37:36,045 --> 00:37:37,297
Don't.

601
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:39,174
Doctor, it's me.

602
00:37:39,883 --> 00:37:41,384
I came back.

603
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:44,888
DONNA: It's like
an outer space Facebook.

604
00:37:44,971 --> 00:37:46,723
Everyone except Rose.

605
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:54,773
(LAUGHING)

606
00:37:54,856 --> 00:37:56,816
DALEK CAAN: He is here.

607
00:37:56,900 --> 00:38:00,570
The Dark Lord is come!

608
00:38:00,653 --> 00:38:04,866
Supreme One, this Subwave Network,
I will address it. Give me access.

609
00:38:07,702 --> 00:38:09,704
-We've lost them.
-No, no, no, no.

610
00:38:09,871 --> 00:38:12,290
There's another signal coming through.
There's someone else out there.

611
00:38:12,373 --> 00:38:14,542
Hello? Can you hear me?

612
00:38:14,626 --> 00:38:15,919
Rose.

613
00:38:17,045 --> 00:38:19,672
Your voice is different and yet

614
00:38:20,507 --> 00:38:24,260
its arrogance is unchanged.

615
00:38:24,344 --> 00:38:25,678
No.

616
00:38:26,679 --> 00:38:28,348
But he's dead.

617
00:38:29,682 --> 00:38:33,311
Welcome to my new empire, Doctor.

618
00:38:34,354 --> 00:38:38,316
It is only fitting that you should
bear witness to the resurrection

619
00:38:38,399 --> 00:38:41,402
and the triumph of Davros,

620
00:38:41,486 --> 00:38:46,282
lord and creator of the Dalek race.

621
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:50,036
Doctor.

622
00:38:50,119 --> 00:38:53,039
DAVROS: Have you nothing to say?

623
00:38:53,122 --> 00:38:55,124
Doctor, it's all right.

624
00:38:55,750 --> 00:38:57,836
We're in the Tardis.

625
00:38:57,919 --> 00:38:59,420
We're safe.

626
00:38:59,921 --> 00:39:02,465
But you were destroyed.

627
00:39:02,549 --> 00:39:05,218
In the very first year of the Time War
at the Gates of Elysium.

628
00:39:05,301 --> 00:39:08,930
I saw your command ship fly
into the jaws of the Nightmare Child.

629
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,348
I tried to save you.

630
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:13,268
But it took one stronger than you.

631
00:39:13,393 --> 00:39:15,770
Dalek Caan himself.

632
00:39:15,937 --> 00:39:19,774
DALEK CAAN:
I flew into the wild and fire.

633
00:39:19,941 --> 00:39:24,153
I danced and died a thousand times.

634
00:39:24,237 --> 00:39:29,158
Emergency temporal shift took him back
into the Time War itself.

635
00:39:29,242 --> 00:39:31,578
But that's impossible!
The entire war is time-locked!

636
00:39:31,661 --> 00:39:33,538
And yet he succeeded.

637
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:37,208
Oh, it cost him his mind, but imagine,

638
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:40,879
a single simple Dalek succeeded

639
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:44,966
where emperors and Time Lords
have failed.

640
00:39:45,758 --> 00:39:50,638
A testament, don't you think,
to my remarkable creations?

641
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:53,975
And you made a new race of Daleks.

642
00:39:54,767 --> 00:39:56,769
I gave myself to them.

643
00:39:57,270 --> 00:39:58,938
Quite literally.

644
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:04,319
Each one grown from a cell
of my own body.

645
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:11,159
New Daleks. True Daleks.

646
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:14,329
I have my children, Doctor.

647
00:40:15,163 --> 00:40:17,957
What do you have now?

648
00:40:18,541 --> 00:40:23,046
After all this time,
everything we saw, everything we lost,

649
00:40:24,339 --> 00:40:26,507
I have only one thing to say to you.

650
00:40:27,342 --> 00:40:28,509
Bye!

651
00:40:32,347 --> 00:40:37,644
SUPREME DALEK: Emergency!
Locate the Tardis! Find the Doctor!

652
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:42,023
He will go to the Earth
to find his precious human allies.

653
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,359
DALEK CAAN: And death is coming.

654
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,320
Oh, I can see it.

655
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:49,280
Everlasting death

656
00:40:49,364 --> 00:40:52,492
for the most faithful companion.

657
00:40:53,368 --> 00:40:57,705
DALEK: Subwave Network rerouted!
New location, Torchwood!

658
00:40:57,789 --> 00:41:00,875
SUPREME DALEK:
Then exterminate them at once!

659
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:03,795
Exterminate Torchwood!

660
00:41:03,878 --> 00:41:05,505
(ALARM BLARING)

661
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:08,174
Gwen.

662
00:41:08,257 --> 00:41:11,803
Dalek saucer heading for the Bay.
They've found us.

663
00:41:11,886 --> 00:41:14,389
Martha, open that Indigo device.
Listen to me.

664
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:17,225
Lift the central panel, there's a string
of numbers that keep changing.

665
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,978
But the fourth number keeps oscillating
between two different digits.

666
00:41:20,061 --> 00:41:23,064
-Tell me what they are.
-It's a four and a nine.

667
00:41:23,147 --> 00:41:27,151
-We could never work out what that was.
-Yeah! That's a teleport base code.

668
00:41:27,235 --> 00:41:30,446
And that's all I need
to get this thing working again.

669
00:41:31,197 --> 00:41:33,783
Oscillating four and nine.

670
00:41:34,701 --> 00:41:36,869
Thank you, Martha Jones.

671
00:41:38,579 --> 00:41:41,582
I gotta go. I gotta find the Doctor.

672
00:41:43,126 --> 00:41:44,752
I'll come back.

673
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:49,716
-I'm coming back.
-Don't worry about us. Just go.

674
00:41:49,799 --> 00:41:52,385
-We'll be fine.
-JACK: You'd better be.

675
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:11,195
Exterminate!

676
00:42:11,279 --> 00:42:13,781
-Exterminate!
-They're here.

677
00:42:14,449 --> 00:42:17,869
MR SMITH: 7ardis heading for vector 7.
Grid reference 6-6...

678
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:19,871
-There are Daleks out there.
-I know.

679
00:42:19,996 --> 00:42:23,791
I'm sorry, but I have got to find
the Doctor.

680
00:42:24,584 --> 00:42:28,129
Don't move, don't leave the house,
don't do anything.

681
00:42:28,254 --> 00:42:30,882
MR SMITH:
I will protect the boy, Sarah Jane.

682
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:33,384
I love you.

683
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:35,136
Remember that.

684
00:42:49,275 --> 00:42:52,820
Control, I need another shift.
Lock me onto the Tardis. Now.

685
00:42:54,614 --> 00:42:57,283
Right, I'm gonna find him.

686
00:42:57,950 --> 00:42:59,410
Wish me luck.

687
00:42:59,494 --> 00:43:01,913
-Oh, good luck!
-Yeah, good luck, sweetheart.

688
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:16,302
It's like a ghost town.

689
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:18,930
DOCTOR: Sarah Jane said
they were taking the people.

690
00:43:19,013 --> 00:43:20,431
What for? Think, Donna.

691
00:43:20,515 --> 00:43:23,643
When you met Rose in that
parallel world, what did she say?

692
00:43:23,726 --> 00:43:26,562
Just, "The darkness is coming."

693
00:43:26,687 --> 00:43:28,231
Anything else?

694
00:43:32,193 --> 00:43:34,695
Why don't you ask her yourself?

695
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:23,995
Exterminate!

696
00:44:37,216 --> 00:44:41,429
I've got you. It missed you.
Look, it's me, Doctor.

697
00:44:41,512 --> 00:44:43,598
-Rose.
-Right.

698
00:44:44,265 --> 00:44:47,602
-(GASPING) Long time no see.
-Yeah.

699
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:49,604
Been busy, you know.

700
00:44:50,271 --> 00:44:52,565
Don't die. No, don't die.

701
00:44:53,900 --> 00:44:55,693
My God, don't die.

702
00:44:57,445 --> 00:45:00,072
Get him into the Tardis, quick. Move!

703
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:05,369
But they don't work against Daleks.

704
00:45:05,453 --> 00:45:11,500
Yeah? Well, I'm going out fighting.
Like Owen, like Tosh. How about you?

705
00:45:13,628 --> 00:45:14,921
Exterminate!

706
00:45:15,004 --> 00:45:16,631
-Yes, ma'am!
-Exterminate!

707
00:45:19,717 --> 00:45:21,886
DONNA: What do we do?

708
00:45:21,969 --> 00:45:24,138
There must be some medicine,
or something.

709
00:45:24,263 --> 00:45:28,309
Just step back.
Rose, do as I say and get back!

710
00:45:28,434 --> 00:45:31,479
He's dying.
And you know what happens next.

711
00:45:31,604 --> 00:45:33,773
-What do you mean?
-He can't.

712
00:45:33,898 --> 00:45:36,359
Not now. I came all this way.

713
00:45:36,442 --> 00:45:38,986
What do you mean? What happens next?

714
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:46,494
It's starting.

715
00:45:53,584 --> 00:45:55,544
(TYRES SCREECHING)

716
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:05,888
All human transport is forbidden!

717
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:07,974
I surrender! I'm sorry!

718
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:12,561
Daleks do not accept apologies!
You will be exterminated!

719
00:46:12,687 --> 00:46:14,814
-Exterminate!
-Exterminate!

720
00:46:22,113 --> 00:46:24,031
Exterminate!

721
00:46:24,365 --> 00:46:26,033
Exterminate!

722
00:46:26,951 --> 00:46:28,536
(SHOUTING)

723
00:46:30,955 --> 00:46:34,417
JACK: Here we go. Good luck, Doctor!

724
00:46:34,542 --> 00:46:36,502
DONNA: Will someone
please tell me what is going on?

725
00:46:36,627 --> 00:46:40,631
When he's dying, his body,
it repairs itself. It changes.

726
00:46:41,257 --> 00:46:42,842
But you can't!

727
00:46:42,925 --> 00:46:45,511
I'm sorry, it's too late.

728
00:46:47,430 --> 00:46:49,598
I'm regenerating.

